          "startTime": 1776868590889
        },
        {
          "text": "In Zig, use `///` (doc comments) placed directly above the field:\n\n```zig\nconst MyStruct = struct {\n    /// Explanation of this field.\n    my_field: u32,\n};\n```\n\n`///` is a doc comment recognized by the compiler and tooling (e.g., `zig doc`). Regular `//` comments also work but won't appear in generated documentation.",
